fontconfig
------------------------------------------
Fontconfig is a library designed to provide system-wide font
configuration, customization and application access.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.1-1
  libexpat1-2.0.1-1
  libfreetype6-2.3.11-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libiconv2-1.13.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.65-1
  automake1.11-1.11.1-1
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.80-1
  docbook-sgml31-3.1-1
  docbook-dsssl-1.79-2
  docbook-utils-0.6.14-1
  gawk-3.1.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  libtool-2.2.7a-15
  make-3.81-2
  pkg-config-0.23b-10
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://fontconfig.org/wiki/

Canonical download:
  http://fontconfig.org/release/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack fontconfig-2.8.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./fontconfig-2.8.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/fontconfig-2.8.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/fontconfig-2.8.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libfontconfig-devel-2.8.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libfontconfig1-2.8.0-X.tar.bz2

For a list of files in each binary package, from the command line
run: 'cygcheck -l [PACKAGE]'.

-------------------------------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 2.8.0-1 -----
Version bump.
